area, and is no longer.

00:01:25.570 --> 00:01:28.000
So I think this will be a
really interesting talk.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.710
So Susan, I think we'll be
introducing, and then Charlie.

00:01:31.710 --> 00:01:36.090
Oh, by the way, this is
a book I got, I think,

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:38.990
40 years ago about
Old Cambridge.

00:01:38.990 --> 00:01:42.580
And now, with the additional
research that's been done,

00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:45.180
we see that they've
made it a lot thicker.

00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:48.630
So a lot of research
has been done, a lot

00:01:48.630 --> 00:01:50.100
of interesting background.

00:01:50.100 --> 00:01:51.746
And I look forward to it.

